There is no existing formula in `M2`, so I need to write one. Because the criteria involve matching one row by Asset ID and filtering columns by date and value threshold across a 2D block, `SUMPRODUCT` is the right compatible LibreOffice/Excel formula.

Logic:
- `(A2:A11=L2)` picks the matching asset row
- `(B1:J1>=M1)` filters dates on/after start
- `(B1:J1<N1)` filters dates before end
- `(B2:J11>100)` filters values above 100
- `SUMPRODUCT` multiplies these boolean arrays and counts matches

I should write the formula to `M2`, save to the output directory with same filename, recalculate, verify `M2`, and ensure sheet name remains `Sheet1`. I’ll also sanity-check expected result from the visible data: Asset 5 is row 6, values from Jan 1 to Jan 6 are [59,110,125,474,908,881], of these >100 are 5, so `M2` should evaluate to 5.
Code:
```repl
import os
from openpyxl import load_workbook

infile = input_spreadsheet
filename = os.path.basename(infile)
outdir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet"
outfile = os.path.join(outdir, filename)

# Load and write formula
wb = load_workbook(infile)
original_sheetnames = wb.sheetnames[:]
ws = wb["Sheet1"]

formula = '=SUMPRODUCT(($A$2:$A$11=$L2)*(B$1:J$1>=$M$1)*(B$1:J$1<$N$1)*(B2:J11>100))'
print("Writing formula to M2:", formula)
print("Pre-write M2:", ws["M2"].value)

ws["M2"] = formula

wb.save(outfile)
print("Saved to:", outfile)

# Recalculate
recalc_result = await recalculate(outfile)
print("Recalculate result:", recalc_result)

# Reload to check sheet names after recalc
wb2 = load_workbook(outfile)
print("Sheet names after recalc:", wb2.sheetnames)
if wb2.sheetnames != original_sheetnames:
    # rename back if changed
    for i, expected in enumerate(original_sheetnames):
        wb2.worksheets[i].title = expected
    wb2.save(outfile)
    print("Renamed sheets back to:", original_sheetnames)

# Verify formula text
wb_formula = load_workbook(outfile, data_only=False)
wsf = wb_formula["Sheet1"]
print("Stored formula in M2:", wsf["M2"].value)

# Verify computed value
wb_val = load_workbook(outfile, data_only=True)
wsv = wb_val["Sheet1"]
print("Verified target/input cells:")
for ref in ["L2", "M1", "N1", "M2"]:
    print(ref, "->", wsv[ref].value)

# Extra sanity check from raw data
asset = wsv["L2"].value
dates = [wsv.cell(1, c).value for c in range(2, 11)]
asset_ids = [wsv.cell(r, 1).value for r in range(2, 12)]
match_row = None
for r in range(2, 12):
    if wsv.cell(r, 1).value == asset:
        match_row = r
        break
print("Matched asset row for", asset, ":", match_row)
if match_row:
    vals = [wsv.cell(match_row, c).value for c in range(2, 11)]
    pairs = list(zip(dates, vals))
    print("Date/value pairs for matched row:", pairs)
    py_count = sum(1 for d, v in pairs if d is not None and v is not None and d >= wsv["M1"].value and d < wsv["N1"].value and v > 100)
    print("Python sanity-check count:", py_count)
